647
00:33:27.983 --> 00:33:30.117
- [Indistinct conversations]
- [Sighs]

648
00:33:34.515 --> 00:33:35.700
[Door opens]

649
00:33:35.711 --> 00:33:38.235
Francis: Okay. and I'm still waiting
for those third-party subpoenas.

650
00:33:38.246 --> 00:33:39.766
Howard: Oh. great. Let me know. then.

651
00:33:39.777 --> 00:33:40.994
- Thanks. Francis.
- All right.

652
00:33:40.996 --> 00:33:43.696
- Julie. what's up?
- From Chuck.

653
00:33:43.698 --> 00:33:45.698
It came via messenger...
the instructions say

654
00:33:45.700 --> 00:33:48.250
he wants you to read
it as soon as possible.

655
00:33:48.859 --> 00:33:50.161
[Door closes]

656
00:33:50.172 --> 00:33:51.414
Mm-hmm.

657
00:33:51.961 --> 00:33:53.706
Uh. here's what I need you to do.

658
00:33:53.708 --> 00:33:57.443
Call around. Find someplace
special for the retirement party.

659
00:33:57.445 --> 00:33:59.312
Something classy. old-school.

660
00:33:59.314 --> 00:34:01.014
Uh. La Posada. maybe.

661
00:34:01.016 --> 00:34:04.325
And a band. Something jazzy. Upbeat.

662
00:34:04.336 --> 00:34:05.492
Find what's available.

663
00:34:05.503 --> 00:34:06.890
- Let's set it up.
- Okay.

664
00:34:06.902 --> 00:34:08.586
[Envelope tearing]

665
00:34:08.958 --> 00:34:10.531
[Door opens]

666
00:34:11.785 --> 00:34:13.242
[Door closes]

667
00:34:20.871 --> 00:34:22.707
Goddamit. Chuck.

668
00:34:22.737 --> 00:34:24.074
[Door opens]

669
00:34:25.160 --> 00:34:27.285
You're suing Hamlin. Hamlin. McGill?

670
00:34:27.296 --> 00:34:29.003
Come on in. Howard.

671
00:34:29.980 --> 00:34:31.275
[Door slams]

672
00:34:31.286 --> 00:34:32.729
[Sizzling]

673
00:34:32.740 --> 00:34:34.386
You turned the lights on.

674
00:34:34.397 --> 00:34:37.917
I told you... I'm back to normal.

675
00:34:37.919 --> 00:34:41.399
And yes. I am suing HHM
for breach of contract.

676
00:34:41.410 --> 00:34:43.418
Do you have any idea what you're doing?

677
00:34:43.429 --> 00:34:45.191
[Sighs] I believe I do.

678
00:34:45.202 --> 00:34:47.160
I'm calling your bluff.

679
00:34:47.162 --> 00:34:49.930
This is my firm. I built it.

680
00:34:49.941 --> 00:34:53.399
Your father was working in a
two-room office when I joined him.

681
00:34:53.401 --> 00:34:56.407
And you I tutored for the bar exam.

682
00:34:56.418 --> 00:34:57.837
You're not kicking me out.

683
00:34:57.839 --> 00:35:00.173
If you can't "trust my
judgment." as you say.

684
00:35:00.175 --> 00:35:01.507
so be it.

685
00:35:01.509 --> 00:35:04.453
but you're gonna have
to pay me for my share.

686
00:35:04.464 --> 00:35:07.513
I believe it comes to around $8 million.

687
00:35:07.515 --> 00:35:10.136
We both know the firm
doesn't have the money.

688
00:35:11.488 --> 00:35:14.422
You'd rather tear down HHM than retire?

689
00:35:14.433 --> 00:35:17.348
You think I'm trouble
now? As your partner?

690
00:35:17.359 --> 00:35:19.449
Imagine me as your enemy.

691
00:35:22.350 --> 00:35:23.870
[Immersion blender whirring]

692
00:35:23.881 --> 00:35:25.214
Chuck...

693
00:35:26.076 --> 00:35:27.600
the damage that you're going to do...

694
00:35:27.602 --> 00:35:29.592
- [Whirring stops]
- If you'd like to discuss this further.

695
00:35:29.603 --> 00:35:31.815
we can... in court.

696
00:35:31.826 --> 00:35:33.406
Until then...

697
00:35:34.256 --> 00:35:36.776
what else is there to say?

698
00:35:37.520 --> 00:35:39.987
[Whirring continues]

699
00:35:45.403 --> 00:35:46.869
[Door opens]

700
00:35:46.881 --> 00:35:48.550
[Door slams]

701
00:35:48.552 --> 00:35:50.303
[Whirring stops]

702
00:35:50.314 --> 00:35:52.061
[Sizzling]

703
00:35:52.740 --> 00:35:55.222
[Sniffles. clears throat]

704
00:35:55.233 --> 00:35:57.263
[Sighs] Blue pot. Red wine.

705
00:35:57.265 --> 00:35:59.065
Black burner.

706
00:35:59.067 --> 00:36:01.100
Blue pot. Red wine.

707
00:36:01.717 --> 00:36:04.834
Black burner. Blue pot.
Red wine. Black burner.

708
00:36:05.998 --> 00:36:07.568
[Clears throat]

709
00:36:08.443 --> 00:36:09.811
[Sighing]

710
00:36:14.025 --> 00:36:17.688
[Air hissing]

711
00:36:25.042 --> 00:36:27.109
[Liquid sloshing]

712
00:36:31.462 --> 00:36:32.928
[Ball taps]

713
00:36:37.653 --> 00:36:39.286
[Liquid sloshing]

714
00:36:53.365 --> 00:36:55.705
[Balls clattering]

715
00:36:55.716 --> 00:36:57.416
Jimmy: I got hot hands.

716
00:36:57.418 --> 00:37:00.161
I got hot hands! I know
this is gonna be the one!

717
00:37:00.172 --> 00:37:02.555
B-9!

718
00:37:02.603 --> 00:37:07.029
Let's hope that biopsy comes back "B-9."

719
00:37:07.040 --> 00:37:08.622
B-9.

720
00:37:09.255 --> 00:37:10.930
[Door opens]

721
00:37:12.013 --> 00:37:14.193
Okay... what's next?

722
00:37:14.204 --> 00:37:15.537
[Air hisses]

723
00:37:15.548 --> 00:37:17.747
We got... I-29.

724
00:37:17.758 --> 00:37:20.138
I remember when I was 29.

725
00:37:20.149 --> 00:37:22.383
Bet you do. too.

726
00:37:22.394 --> 00:37:24.725
I-29.

727
00:37:30.411 --> 00:37:34.005
Here comes O-62.

728
00:37:34.982 --> 00:37:36.689
Oh. my God.

729
00:37:36.691 --> 00:37:39.036
Have I called 62 of
these already? [Chuckling]

730
00:37:39.047 --> 00:37:42.161
It feels like it. O-62.

731
00:37:43.138 --> 00:37:45.372
Here we have B-2.

732
00:37:45.383 --> 00:37:46.818
B-2.

733
00:37:46.829 --> 00:37:49.535
Well. tonight is all bingo.

734
00:37:49.537 --> 00:37:50.880
Here it comes.

735
00:37:50.891 --> 00:37:53.539
O-70. Anyone? O-70.

736
00:37:54.161 --> 00:37:56.263
All right. No takers.

737
00:37:56.274 --> 00:37:57.818
Boom!

738
00:37:58.380 --> 00:37:59.979
G-55.

739
00:37:59.981 --> 00:38:01.381
G-55.

740
00:38:01.383 --> 00:38:03.049
Oh. my God! Bingo!

741
00:38:03.051 --> 00:38:04.388
- I got bingo!
- [Applause]

742
00:38:04.399 --> 00:38:06.619
Big Paul. bring it up.

743
00:38:06.621 --> 00:38:08.291
Kelly. take a look.

744
00:38:08.302 --> 00:38:10.771
- [Applause continues]
- We may have a winner.

745
00:38:11.353 --> 00:38:14.208
Kelly. tell me... have we got it?

746
00:38:14.219 --> 00:38:15.515
We have a bingo!

747
00:38:15.526 --> 00:38:17.993
Paul. step up to the winner's circle.

748
00:38:18.004 --> 00:38:19.372
Let's hear it for him!

749
00:38:19.383 --> 00:38:21.616
Let's give him a big round of applause!

750
00:38:21.627 --> 00:38:23.894
[Applause]

751
00:38:23.905 --> 00:38:26.239
Okay. New game. new cards.

752
00:38:26.241 --> 00:38:27.740
Here they come.

753
00:38:27.742 --> 00:38:30.122
Get yourself some new cards. New cards.

754
00:38:30.169 --> 00:38:31.778
[Microphone feedback]

755
00:38:31.780 --> 00:38:34.370
The helpers have them.
You can have one. two.

756
00:38:34.381 --> 00:38:36.685
You can have up to four. as you know.

757
00:38:37.083 --> 00:38:39.877
Here's a lucky blue one for you.

758
00:38:39.888 --> 00:38:43.388
All right. Take your cards
so we can start a new game.

759
00:38:43.390 --> 00:38:46.357
There you go. Add that to your stack.

760
00:38:47.490 --> 00:38:49.027
All right. Get your cards.

761
00:38:49.029 --> 00:38:51.580
Hey. Irene. you feeling lucky today?

762
00:38:51.591 --> 00:38:53.198
I-I guess so.

763
00:38:53.200 --> 00:38:55.934
[Chuckling] All right.
Well. here's one on me...

764
00:38:55.936 --> 00:38:57.402
just for you.

765
00:38:58.208 --> 00:39:03.302
All right. I sold my
soul for B-I-N-G-and-O!

766
00:39:03.810 --> 00:39:06.341
Let's clear the table.

767
00:39:06.352 --> 00:39:08.966
[Indistinct conversations]

768
00:39:10.391 --> 00:39:12.029
[Sniffles]

769
00:39:21.203 --> 00:39:25.330
