770
00:39:25.867 --> 00:39:27.352
Load it up.

771
00:39:27.922 --> 00:39:31.135
[Balls clattering]

772
00:39:31.137 --> 00:39:33.104
♪ ♪

773
00:39:33.844 --> 00:39:35.573
Locked and loaded.

774
00:39:35.575 --> 00:39:37.211
[Cabinet door closes]

775
00:39:37.222 --> 00:39:38.735
[Sighs]

776
00:39:42.648 --> 00:39:44.667
Here comes a new game.

777
00:39:44.678 --> 00:39:45.911
[Switch clicks]

778
00:39:45.922 --> 00:39:49.420
♪ ♪

779
00:39:49.422 --> 00:39:51.923
First number up...

780
00:39:51.925 --> 00:39:53.903
♪ ♪

781
00:39:53.914 --> 00:39:56.519
it's N-31.

782
00:39:56.530 --> 00:39:58.070
"N" for "Nancy."

783
00:39:58.081 --> 00:40:01.294
31 for the number of times
she told me to take a hike.

784
00:40:01.305 --> 00:40:04.242
N-31.

785
00:40:04.253 --> 00:40:06.466
♪ ♪

786
00:40:06.477 --> 00:40:08.255
G-48.

787
00:40:08.266 --> 00:40:10.719
"G" for the Greatest Generation.

788
00:40:10.730 --> 00:40:13.845
48 for "Dewey Defeats Truman."

789
00:40:13.847 --> 00:40:17.380
Here's I-25... the big "I."

790
00:40:17.391 --> 00:40:18.934
I-25.

791
00:40:18.984 --> 00:40:22.854
It's B-12. like the vitamin.

792
00:40:22.856 --> 00:40:26.662
♪ ♪

793
00:40:30.907 --> 00:40:32.497
O-67!

794
00:40:32.499 --> 00:40:35.642
Anybody? I got a good
feeling about this.

795
00:40:35.653 --> 00:40:38.243
O-67!

796
00:40:40.087 --> 00:40:43.467
I-I-I think... Bingo!

797
00:40:43.478 --> 00:40:44.742
Who is that?

798
00:40:44.744 --> 00:40:46.314
Come on up.

799
00:40:47.071 --> 00:40:51.271
Irene! Irene. come on up here. dear.

800
00:40:51.282 --> 00:40:53.990
Bring it up to Kelly. Let's take a look.

801
00:40:54.001 --> 00:40:56.254
Kelly has to check your card.

802
00:40:56.256 --> 00:40:58.079
[Balls clattering]

803
00:40:58.090 --> 00:41:00.190
Here she comes.

804
00:41:00.201 --> 00:41:03.954
♪ ♪

805
00:41:04.743 --> 00:41:06.587
Could be...

806
00:41:07.376 --> 00:41:09.233
♪ ♪

807
00:41:09.235 --> 00:41:11.536
Oh. my goodness.

808
00:41:11.538 --> 00:41:15.506
It is a bingo for Irene!

809
00:41:15.508 --> 00:41:17.709
Let's hear it for Irene Landry!

810
00:41:17.711 --> 00:41:19.571
[Scattered applause]

811
00:41:19.587 --> 00:41:22.775
Give it up for the big
winner. Irene Landry!

812
00:41:22.786 --> 00:41:24.415
[Scattered applause continues]

813
00:41:24.417 --> 00:41:26.697
Fastest bingo of the night!

814
00:41:26.708 --> 00:41:29.187
Come on. Let's hear it for Irene.

815
00:41:29.189 --> 00:41:30.473
- Oh!
- [Thumps]

816
00:41:31.075 --> 00:41:32.123
[Crying]

817
00:41:32.125 --> 00:41:33.325
Irene...

818
00:41:33.336 --> 00:41:34.384
- where ya goin'?
- [Door opens]

819
00:41:34.395 --> 00:41:36.591
Hey. you know what? Take over.

820
00:41:38.137 --> 00:41:40.365
Okay. Time for a new game.

821
00:41:40.367 --> 00:41:43.251
Uh. let's get some
cards out for everyone.

822
00:41:43.262 --> 00:41:44.630
[Crying]

823
00:41:44.641 --> 00:41:46.130
[Door opens]

824
00:41:48.786 --> 00:41:50.124
[Chuckling] Hey.

825
00:41:50.135 --> 00:41:52.207
What's going on? You okay?

826
00:41:52.218 --> 00:41:54.018
[Crying]

827
00:41:54.153 --> 00:41:56.220
Aww. Don't do that.

828
00:41:56.231 --> 00:41:59.153
Your mascara's gonna run all over.

829
00:41:59.164 --> 00:42:01.384
[Crying continues]

830
00:42:01.395 --> 00:42:03.588
Irene. come on.

831
00:42:03.590 --> 00:42:05.348
What's wrong?

832
00:42:05.759 --> 00:42:07.225
[Sniffles]

833
00:42:07.227 --> 00:42:09.848
They've all turned on me.

834
00:42:09.859 --> 00:42:11.169
[Crying]

835
00:42:11.180 --> 00:42:12.780
Who has?

836
00:42:13.233 --> 00:42:14.931
My friends!

837
00:42:14.968 --> 00:42:18.142
Helen. Rose. Myrtle.

838
00:42:18.153 --> 00:42:20.470
All of them.

839
00:42:20.481 --> 00:42:22.931
What? No!

840
00:42:22.942 --> 00:42:24.950
Yes!

841
00:42:24.966 --> 00:42:26.244
[Sniffles]

842
00:42:26.246 --> 00:42:28.598
They're so cold.

843
00:42:29.739 --> 00:42:33.533
When I walk past them.
they stop talking.

844
00:42:33.535 --> 00:42:35.411
I-I-I hear them whispering

845
00:42:35.422 --> 00:42:38.256
when... when they think I'm not there.

846
00:42:38.258 --> 00:42:40.856
It's just so...

847
00:42:41.027 --> 00:42:42.580
- It's so cruel.
- Mnh.

848
00:42:42.591 --> 00:42:44.762
And I don't even know why.

849
00:42:45.341 --> 00:42:47.794
[Sighs]

850
00:42:49.747 --> 00:42:52.036
I think. uh...

851
00:42:52.038 --> 00:42:54.138
maybe I do.

852
00:42:55.947 --> 00:42:57.812
- You do?
- [Sighs]

853
00:42:59.312 --> 00:43:01.279
[Sighs]

854
00:43:01.290 --> 00:43:03.865
Could it be the settlement?

855
00:43:03.876 --> 00:43:06.560
I mean. maybe they... [Inhales sharply]

856
00:43:06.571 --> 00:43:08.943
want the money.

857
00:43:08.954 --> 00:43:12.474
you know. to improve their lives?

858
00:43:12.485 --> 00:43:15.660
I had no idea any of them needed money.

859
00:43:15.662 --> 00:43:17.862
No one said anything to me.

860
00:43:17.864 --> 00:43:20.364
Well. maybe it's not
about the money itself.

861
00:43:20.366 --> 00:43:24.836
I mean... hello... who
wouldn't want more money?

862
00:43:24.838 --> 00:43:27.407
I mean. maybe it's the idea

863
00:43:27.418 --> 00:43:32.563
that they don't think you're
considering them. you know?

864
00:43:33.220 --> 00:43:35.346
Thinking of their needs?

865
00:43:35.348 --> 00:43:37.749
I-I-I didn't know.

866
00:43:37.751 --> 00:43:41.079
I don't want to hurt
them. They're my friends.

867
00:43:41.090 --> 00:43:42.956
[Breathing heavily]

868
00:43:44.024 --> 00:43:46.491
I wish we never even
started this lawsuit.

869
00:43:46.493 --> 00:43:49.576
I just want everything
to go back the way it was.

870
00:43:49.587 --> 00:43:51.863
[Breathing heavily]

871
00:43:52.587 --> 00:43:55.282
What should I do?

872
00:43:55.978 --> 00:43:58.517
What would you do?

873
00:44:00.673 --> 00:44:04.181
I mean. you know I'm
not a lawyer right now.

874
00:44:04.931 --> 00:44:06.711
Please?

875
00:44:08.172 --> 00:44:10.243
Should I settle?

876
00:44:11.860 --> 00:44:13.684
[Sighs]

877
00:44:14.579 --> 00:44:16.354
Irene...

878
00:44:18.368 --> 00:44:19.761
[Sighs]

879
00:44:19.772 --> 00:44:21.884
you listen to your heart.

880
00:44:34.038 --> 00:44:35.940
Uh. time?

881
00:44:35.942 --> 00:44:37.208
Two hours out.

882
00:44:37.210 --> 00:44:38.743
When did I say I was gonna leave?

883
00:44:38.745 --> 00:44:40.411
20 minutes ago.

884
00:44:41.148 --> 00:44:43.675
Uh. can I have some more coffee. please?

885
00:44:43.686 --> 00:44:45.499
Coming.

886
00:44:50.490 --> 00:44:53.482
Uh. I'm missing a survey
history in this one.

887
00:44:53.493 --> 00:44:56.021
- On it. Sorry about that.
- [Sighs]

888
00:44:56.032 --> 00:44:57.568
- [Coffee pouring]
- Not a problem.

889
00:44:57.579 --> 00:44:59.263
- [Door opens]
- Jimmy: Hey!

890
00:44:59.265 --> 00:45:01.766
Who's ready to have her life changed?

891
00:45:01.768 --> 00:45:03.301
Kim. did you hear me?

892
00:45:03.303 --> 00:45:05.369
Yep. Heard you. Life changed.

893
00:45:05.380 --> 00:45:09.173
[Chuckles] Stop your work.
both of you. for a sec.

894
00:45:09.175 --> 00:45:10.842
I-I got big. big news.

895
00:45:10.844 --> 00:45:12.677
Can you just tell us later. Jimmy?

896
00:45:12.679 --> 00:45:15.428
- I'm so late. it's not even funny.
- Mesa Verde can wait.

897
00:45:15.439 --> 00:45:18.282
- Look. I got Zafiro.
- It's not Mesa Verde.

898
00:45:18.284 --> 00:45:20.651
It's a new client. and if I mess
this up. it's a former client.

899
00:45:20.653 --> 00:45:22.753
I thought Mesa Verde
was your one and only.

900
00:45:22.755 --> 00:45:24.655
You know. it's go...
Ji... uh. I'm sorry.

901
00:45:24.666 --> 00:45:26.681
Jimmy. can I just explain
all this to you later? I'm...

902
00:45:26.692 --> 00:45:28.900
Sandpiper is settling.

903
00:45:29.529 --> 00:45:31.850
- What?
- [Chuckling] Yeah.

904
00:45:31.861 --> 00:45:33.493
For a bundle.

905
00:45:34.392 --> 00:45:36.200
But th-they can't be settling.

906
00:45:36.202 --> 00:45:38.202
[Chuckling] Class actions
don't move that fast.

907
00:45:38.204 --> 00:45:40.438
Don't get bogged down in the details!

908
00:45:40.463 --> 00:45:43.181
Trust me... they're settling!

909
00:45:44.748 --> 00:45:46.014
- Wow. that...
- [Both chuckle]

910
00:45:46.025 --> 00:45:47.793
- Yeah. Yeah!
- That's great. then.

911
00:45:47.804 --> 00:45:49.647
So. hey. let's celebrate.

912
00:45:49.649 --> 00:45:51.176
I can tell that you...

913
00:45:51.187 --> 00:45:53.484
pulled another
all-nighter here. you know?

914
00:45:53.486 --> 00:45:56.020
You... you got to stop
and smell the roses.

915
00:45:56.022 --> 00:45:59.023
Hey. who's got two
thumbs. a bottle of Zafiro.

916
00:45:59.025 --> 00:46:00.957
and 20% of the common fund?!

917
00:46:00.968 --> 00:46:02.159
- Huh?
- This guy!

918
00:46:02.161 --> 00:46:04.629
I know... you do. Uh. I
am happy for you. Jimmy.

919
00:46:04.631 --> 00:46:05.963
Be happy for us!

920
00:46:05.965 --> 00:46:08.277
This is the solution to everything.

921
00:46:08.288 --> 00:46:09.812
Okay. Francesca. could you
just put these all in my car?

922
00:46:09.823 --> 00:46:11.351
Kim.

923
00:46:11.362 --> 00:46:12.621
Yeah. Jimmy. I gotta go.

924
00:46:12.632 --> 00:46:14.527
Gimme five goddamn minutes.

925
00:46:14.538 --> 00:46:16.288
- I don't have five minutes.
- But you're already late.

926
00:46:16.299 --> 00:46:19.043
What's five more minutes?
So drive 60 instead of 55.

927
00:46:19.045 --> 00:46:20.656
- [Chuckling] Jimmy!
- What?

928
00:46:20.667 --> 00:46:22.166
- [Door opens]
- You're not hearing me.

929
00:46:22.177 --> 00:46:24.015
Our troubles are over! Come on!

930
00:46:24.017 --> 00:46:25.738
Jimmy. I'm leaving now.

931
00:46:25.749 --> 00:46:27.018
I'll be back in a few hours.

932
00:46:27.029 --> 00:46:28.218
Think of all the things
you want to say to me.

933
00:46:28.229 --> 00:46:29.845
and just say them to me later. okay?

934
00:46:29.856 --> 00:46:31.234
Bye.

935
00:46:31.245 --> 00:46:32.606
[Door closes]

936
00:46:37.863 --> 00:46:39.410
[Door opens]

937
00:46:41.465 --> 00:46:42.770
[Door closes]

938
00:46:42.781 --> 00:46:44.885
You. Shots.

939
00:46:44.919 --> 00:46:47.303
- Uh. I...
- Shots.

940
00:46:47.314 --> 00:46:49.180
We're celebrating.

941
00:46:55.154 --> 00:46:57.348
- Cheers.
- [Glasses clink]

942
00:46:58.717 --> 00:47:00.604
[Slurps]

943
00:47:00.615 --> 00:47:01.896
Smooth.

944
00:47:01.907 --> 00:47:03.554
[Exhales sharply]

945
00:47:03.556 --> 00:47:05.089
[Tapping counter]

946
00:47:05.091 --> 00:47:06.506
Yeah.

947
00:47:11.060 --> 00:47:15.032
Under the terms we're offering.
you get a substantial payment

948
00:47:15.034 --> 00:47:18.323
without any impact to your property
via drilling and extraction.

949
00:47:18.334 --> 00:47:19.704
And rather than waiting years to close.

950
00:47:19.706 --> 00:47:23.385
Mr. Gatwood is offering cash
on the barrel. right now.

951
00:47:23.396 --> 00:47:26.487
Given the cost of overhead. liabilities.

952
00:47:26.498 --> 00:47:28.779
and other burdens Mr. Gatwood assumes.

953
00:47:28.781 --> 00:47:31.342
we believe this offer is more than fair.

954
00:47:31.353 --> 00:47:32.949
We believe...

955
00:47:33.436 --> 00:47:36.951
we believe this offer is more than fair.

956
00:47:50.236 --> 00:47:51.890
[Gasps]

957
00:47:51.901 --> 00:47:55.429
[Air rushing]

958
00:47:56.046 --> 00:47:59.437
[Breathing heavily]

959
00:48:05.336 --> 00:48:07.656
[Door creaks]

960
00:48:13.760 --> 00:48:17.094
[Whimpers]

961
00:48:18.304 --> 00:48:19.989
Aah!

962
00:48:20.000 --> 00:48:24.402
[Breathing shakily]

963
00:48:41.387 --> 00:48:44.755
[Wind whistling]

964
00:48:58.251 --> 00:49:03.005
